comments: The Prim.Ordering module is embedded in the PureScript compiler. Unlike `Prim`, it is not imported implicitly. It contains a type level `Ordering` data structure.

declarations.comments:
The `Ordering` kind represents the three possibilities of comparing two
types of the same kind: `LT` (less than), `EQ` (equal to), and
`GT` (greater than).
declarations.title: Ordering

name: Prim.Ordering
